Absolutely horrible horrible service. I placed an order via grubhub at 6pm only to receive it one hour and 45 minutes later. I was on the verge of cancelling when my food arrived. When I asked the driver what was the reason for the hold up, boy did I receive an EARFUL! It seems that Buffalo Boss prioritizes their in house orders over everything else and they make outgoing deliveries wait until the end. But there was an issue i find more disturbing.The driver believed that the cashier was purposefully trying to make him wait unnecessarily for the order because of an apparent dislike the staff seem to have for delivery personnel. He said after the first 15 minutes of him arriving and showing the order to be picked up to the young lady, he reminded her of the order after seeing several customers who, having came in after him, leave with their orders before him. After 30 minutes he asked again about the order and she blew him off. That order should have been more than ready by that time. After 45 minutes he inquired again as to what was the reason for the hold up at which time she began screaming at him. After a total of about 60 minutes and watching about 12 people who came in after him leave before him. He finally got the order. He said she was smiling the entire time as if she was trying to drag out the time on purpose. I wondered why would their employee behave in such a manner but then I remembered something. When I ordered from them on Superbowl Sunday my food was also late and barely warm and even though a wait was to be expected, I also was told by the delivery driver at that time about how unpleasant the staff are to deal with and how they overhear staff saying that they hate them and cannot stand seeing them because it gives them unnecessary work. I don't know if the same lady was working that night, or if the staff are purposely trying to make the experience so bad for these delivery people that they don't want to come back. Whatever the reason, it is your paying customers that suffer. The quality of your staff reflects on you. People tend to act a certain way when there is either no managerial oversight, or if they are assured that such behavior will not result in repercussion. I was not there personally, but two similar  complaints from delivery drivers in such a short time leads me to write this. I was also sent a picture of the staff member involved. As you can see she is not even wearing a hair net with her hair going all the way down to the back while handling food. That is not acceptable. I don't know what class of people run this establishment, but on so many levels, you really need to do better. I will also be posting the same review on yelp.

Love it!!! It's 5 stars. But, pricing can be better. So, deducted 1 star, there's always room for improvement. Now, let's talk wings. Everytime I stop by 3 or 4 people stop in to pick up personal or group orders. It's pretty impressive, employees seem to lnow their name. Clearly Buffalo Boss, is just that, the boss. The chicken is advertised as organic. 12 different sauces to choose from. Each time I come here, I try a different flavor. Medium sauce still comes up the winner for me. Napkins, napkins, not everyone gives in to licking their fingers. But, these wings, the sauce from Buffalo Wings, do tempt you to do that, at least want to. Fries are served up plentiful. There may be a motive behind it,  the generous portion of fries takes the focus off the money you spent for 2 tenders or 6 little wings, ouch! It's good though. So you can get your money's worth, you might want to upgrade the wing quantity. Their open till 12Mid during the week and 1am on the weekends. Their attached to every popular delivery service., you can think of, 7 in all. 2 high tables and chairs, 2 small tables and stools against the window, makes for a cafe type of setting. But, everyone's there to eat their food and go. Until, they linger in respect for the flavor,.Yep, this chicken demainds you slow down your pace and enjoy the experience of eating the Buffalo Boss wings, messy but good. I'm not from Brooklyn. But, even I wanted to call in an order to go and, share with my friends. But, the commute won't allow it. Buffalo Boss a must on your To Do List.
